text: The Rudolph and Louise Ebert House is located in Fond du Lac, Wisconsin. ==History== Rudolph Ebert was a bank president and local politician. As known as the 'Pink Lady', the house was listed on the State Register of Historic Places in 2001 and on the National Register of Historic Places the following year. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Wisconsin Category:National Register of Historic Places in Fond du Lac County, Wisconsin Category:Houses in Fond du Lac County, Wisconsin Category:Queen Anne architecture in Wisconsin Category:Houses completed in 1892
